-- Odebrecht Wins $523 Million Brazil Water Deal, BN Americas Says
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-05-24T16:14:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-24/odebrecht-wins-523-million-brazil-water-deal-bn-americas-says.html
Consorcio Centro-Oeste, a group of
Brazilian companies led by Odebrecht SA, has won a 1.07 billion-real ($522.5 million) contract to provide water and sewerage
services in four municipalities, Business News Americas said,
citing Robson Borges Salazar, financial director of the water
utility that granted the concession.  Construtora Norberto Odebrecht SA, Foz do Brasil SA and
Central do Brasil will build infrastructure and improve services
in Aparecida de Goiania, Trindade, Rio Verde and Jatai for water
utility Saneamento de Goias SA, Business News Americas said
yesterday in the  report .  The group will have to provide sewerage services for all
clients that receive potable water within six years, according
to the report. The contract hasnâ€™t been signed yet.  To contact the reporter on this story:
